result.execSummary:
The defendant Alexander M Midstokke was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manufacture/Deliver THC (<=200g), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(h)1.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Alexander M Midstokke in court with attorney Roger L Klopp.  Brenda L Yaskal appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Waiver of Preliminary Hearing filed. Court found probable cause, bound defendant over. Information filed, reading waived. Court went over the rights & elements. Defendant plead no contest to count one in 14CF139. Court found defendant guilty, entered judgment, sentence withheld, 2 yrs. probation, conds: $518 costs, inclusive of DNA surcharge, submit DNA sample, continue with school until obtaining diploma or other equivalency, six month review of case - to be enrolled in AODA at that time, complete AODA and follow all treatment recommendations. Defendant may petition Court in writing, after two years, for expunction of record, contingent upon successful completion of probation, no new law violations and costs paid in full. No jail credit.  Court read in and dismissed counts 2&3 and 14CF61. Restitution hearing to be set. Case called 3:11 p.m., adjourned 3:35 p.m.
